⸻

Exact service responsibilities

api-gateway

External REST API for frontend and CLI.
Responsibilities:
	•	auth enforcement
	•	request validation
	•	rate limiting
	•	fan-out to internal gRPC

auth-service

Start simple:
	•	local users + passwordless email or OIDC
	•	org membership
	•	RBAC

Roles:
	•	owner
	•	admin
	•	developer
	•	operator
	•	viewer

project-service
	•	create/update/delete projects
	•	attach repos
	•	manage runtime profiles
	•	manage templates

task-service
	•	create task DAG
	•	store acceptance criteria
	•	queue runnable tasks
	•	dependency resolution

computer-service

Most important service.
Responsibilities:
	•	allocate host node
	•	create/destroy Firecracker VM
	•	attach workspace volume
	•	start guest agent handshake
	•	pause/resume
	•	branch child VM from snapshot
	•	stream terminal/websocket endpoints

snapshot-service
	•	create VM snapshot manifests
	•	persist workspace/image references
	•	restore from snapshot
	•	GC old snapshots by retention policy

artifact-service
	•	upload/download objects to MinIO
	•	signed internal URLs
	•	metadata
	•	dedup by sha256

policy-service
	•	capability grants
	•	egress policy
	•	allowed images
	•	package install policy
	•	secret mount policy
	•	per-org quotas

agent-orchestrator

This runs the Ralph-style loop and Temporal workflows.
Sub-agents:
	•	planner
	•	allocator
	•	operator
	•	verifier coordinator
	•	recovery manager

verifier-service

Runs checks outside the worker agent:
	•	shell assertions
	•	unit/integration tests
	•	HTTP checks
	•	Playwright tests
	•	visual snapshots
	•	schema validation

browser-service

Optional remote browser helpers:
	•	VNC/noVNC stream
	•	screenshot capture
	•	browser trace export
	•	DOM snapshots

model-gateway

LiteLLM-based gateway in front of:
	•	vLLM
	•	Ollama
	•	optional external APIs

telemetry-collector

OTel collectors, trace correlation, machine lifecycle metrics, task metrics.

⸻

Agent design

Agent roles

1. Planner agent

Input:
	•	user goal
	•	project metadata
	•	repo state
	•	template policies

Output:
	•	PRD fragment
	•	task DAG
	•	runtime requirements
	•	verification specs
	•	budget envelope

2. Allocator

Prefer deterministic code, not LLM.
Decides:
	•	reuse current VirtualPC?
	•	spawn new VirtualPC?
	•	use child VM?
	•	use nested containers only?
	•	task priority and resource class

3. Operator agent

Acts inside a VirtualPC.
Allowed actions:
	•	shell
	•	file ops
	•	browser ops
	•	start/stop nested containers
	•	git
	•	package installation if policy allows

4. Verifier agent

Creates or selects verification procedures but does not mark pass itself.

5. Recovery agent

On failure:
	•	collect diagnostics
	•	restart service
	•	revert to snapshot
	•	fork to child VM
	•	narrow the task
	•	request human review

⸻

Ralph-style loop specification

Each task executes through bounded iterations.

Iteration algorithm
	1.	Load task and latest verified machine state
	2.	Restore memory package:
	•	project brief
	•	decision log
	•	previous failures
	•	current task card
	•	current repo diff
	3.	Save pre-iteration snapshot if configured
	4.	Run operator for max N actions or T minutes
	5.	Persist:
	•	command log
	•	file diff summary
	•	container state
	•	screenshots
	•	artifacts
	6.	Trigger verifier
	7.	If verifier passes:
	•	mark task passed
	8.	If verifier fails:
	•	write failure memo
	•	decide retry / rollback / fork / escalate
	9.	Stop after retry cap or budget cap

Suggested limits
	•	max iteration wall time: 10 minutes
	•	max shell commands: 50
	•	max browser actions: 100
	•	max retries per task: 5
	•	mandatory verifier after every iteration that changes state materially

⸻

Guest image specification

Base guest OS
	•	Ubuntu minimal
	•	systemd enabled
	•	SSH disabled by default
	•	serial console enabled
	•	journald persistent logs
	•	qemu-guest-agent not required if using your own sidecar

Required packages
	•	bash, zsh optional
	•	git
	•	curl, wget, jq
	•	python3 + uv
	•	node + pnpm
	•	docker or nerdctl + containerd inside guest
	•	playwright deps
	•	chromium
	•	tmux
	•	ripgrep
	•	build-essential
	•	sqlite3
	•	psmisc, procps, htop
	•	supervisor/systemd units for guest agent

Guest services
	•	virtualpc-agentd
	•	virtualpc-capd
	•	virtualpc-log-forwarder
	•	virtualpc-snapshot-hook
	•	virtualpc-browserd optional

